body:
@bolkedebruin I think I've fixed the last test. Let me know if those were the sort of tests you were thinking about.

BTW, is it normal that everything is empty in the warehouse when testing? By looking at [these] tests I got the impression that the Airflow db was meant to be there (but it's not).

Also: what do you think about upgrading the Hive version? The current one is ridded with pesky bugs, such as [this] which I encountered while writing the tests.

@artwr Thanks, but I'd have to wait at least 20 minutes anyway. I would love to have a container somewhere that speeds up testing cases such as this (not saying it's easy or that you folks should do that).

[these]: https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/blob/c7a472ed6b0d8a4720f57ba1140c8cf665757167/tests/operators/hive_operator.py#L46
[this]: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-12200

@bolkedebruin 
So the Python 3 tests seem to be going fine, but 2.7 gives me a timezone error. Is there something I should be aware of? https://travis-ci.org/apache/incubator-airflow/jobs/370751659

@Fokko Do you see something in the test code that clearly violates something in 2.7 and that could explain the failing tests? I'm using `DEFAULT_DATE = datetime.datetime(2015, 1, 1)` as start and end date, which is timezone unaware.
